Food.create(name: 'Baked Halibut with Chimichurri', description: 'Though you might normally associate chimichurri with grilled steaks, lamb chops and other robust cuts of meat, this garlicky South American herb sauce pairs wonderfully with mild halibut and other lean white fish. Rubbed over the fillets before baking, the flavor of the chimichurri stays fresh and bright, infusing the delicate fish with a pop of green color and taste that says SPRING! It’s another simple yet impressive fish recipe to add to your repertoire.', recipe_url: 'https://www.thekitchn.com/recipe-baked-chimichurri-halibut-recipes-from-the-kitchn-188598', image_url: 'https://cdn.apartmenttherapy.info/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:eco,c_fit,w_1460/https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.googleapis.com%2Fgen-atmedia%2F3%2F2013%2F04%2F776b41009266678a4ce808fa766dd2aa11224e9f.jpeg', mood_id: 1)
Food.create(name: 'Vietnamese Beef Noodle Pho', description: 'Vietnamese beef noodle pho is an easy soup to fall in love with. Those chewy noodles, that savory broth, the tender slices of beef — all those crunchy, spicy, herby garnishes we get to toss on top. On a cold evening, after a rough day at work, when we’re sick, on a lazy weekend afternoon — a bowl of piping hot pho is pretty much always a good idea.', recipe_url: 'https://www.thekitchn.com/how-to-make-quick-vietnamese-beef-pho-cooking-lessons-from-the-kitchn-215118', image_url: 'https://cdn.apartmenttherapy.info/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:eco,c_fit,w_1460/https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.googleapis.com%2Fgen-atmedia%2F3%2F2015%2F01%2Feb84435688acfbb9c988f165b754bb3a989df6b5.jpeg', mood_id: 2)
Food.create(name: 'Easy Slow Cooker Beef Stroganoff', description: 'Family-friendly classics don’t have to start with a can of condensed soup. This easy beef stroganoff is just as comforting as the one you grew up with, but is made with fresh mushrooms and a simple gravy that comes together as the ingredients braise in the slow cooker. It requires minimal upfront prep (no stovetop browning!), meaning you can toss in all the ingredients in the morning and then return to a warm dinner in the evening.', recipe_url: 'https://www.thekitchn.com/slow-cooker-beef-stroganoff-265025', image_url: 'https://cdn.apartmenttherapy.info/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:eco,c_fit,w_1460/https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.googleapis.com%2Fgen-atmedia%2F3%2F2019%2F01%2Fe1ea1acf00ff5d98f8deed1b2c8223af59a5c09c.jpeg', mood_id: 3)
Food.create(name: 'Bubble and Squeak', description: 'Bubble and squeak, with its cutesy name, is a classic British day-after-holiday dish. It is incredibly versatile, as you can throw in any leftover vegetables or mashed potatoes into this comforting recipe — perfect for a relaxing meal after a hectic Thanksgiving.', recipe_url: 'https://www.thekitchn.com/recipe-bubble-and-squeak-recipes-from-the-kitchn-213148', image_url: 'https://cdn.apartmenttherapy.info/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:eco,c_fit,w_1460/https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.googleapis.com%2Fgen-atmedia%2F3%2F2014%2F11%2Fd2232838000d100ee9863248086dfb367e4a551e.jpeg', mood_id: 4)
Food.create(name: 'Chicken & Dumplings', description: 'On a busy weekend day when you have a lot of things to take care of around the house but not much time to devote to dinner, pull this slow cooker chicken and dumpling recipe out of your back pocket. This comforting dish — with tender chicken swimming in a creamy sauce filled with herbs and vegetables that’s topped with tender dumplings — requires very little attention on your part, but you’re rewarded with a dinner that tastes like you’ve been standing at the stove all day.', recipe_url: 'https://www.thekitchn.com/recipe-slow-cooker-chicken-amp-dumplings-253309', image_url: 'https://cdn.apartmenttherapy.info/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:eco,c_fit,w_1460/https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.googleapis.com%2Fgen-atmedia%2F3%2F2018%2F01%2Ffef187547dd879130efed81d02568b2e5efaacb3.jpeg', mood_id: 5)
Food.create(name: 'Kale Salad with Apricots, Avocado & Parmesan', description: 'I’ve been eating this salad of raw kale tossed in a red wine vinaigrette almost every day for the past month. I love the way the chewy bits of dried apricots and the creamy avocado contrast with the heartiness of the kale. A handful of almonds, a spoonful of beans, and a few flakes of salty parmesan turn this salad into a very satisfying meal. Yes, I thought it high time this recipe was shared.', recipe_url: 'https://www.thekitchn.com/lunch-for-one-kale-salad-with-148328', image_url: 'https://www.thekitchn.com/lunch-for-one-kale-salad-with-148328', mood_id: 6)
Food.create(name: 'Green Eggs and Ham', description: 'Leave it to Dr. Seuss to inspire a breakfast as whimsical and cheery as green eggs and ham. It’s probably safe to say since the book Green Eggs and Ham was published in 1960, parents have been trying to find a way to create the titular dish for eager children.', recipe_url: 'https://www.thekitchn.com/how-to-make-green-eggs-and-ham-242334', image_url: 'https://cdn.apartmenttherapy.info/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:eco,c_fit,w_1460/https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.googleapis.com%2Fgen-atmedia%2F3%2F2017%2F03%2F736d92e150f7619f79df76992250b842a480331b.jpeg', mood_id: 7)
Food.create(name: 'Scallops', description: 'Scallops are a little luxury in my household. A weekend date night means plates of pasta and scallops with wedges of lemon and glasses of white wine on the side. Scallops are sustainable, delicious, and so easy! Here’s how to make quick-cooking scallops on the stovetop in just about five minutes.', recipe_url: 'https://www.thekitchn.com/how-to-cook-scallops-on-the-stovetop-cooking-lessons-from-the-kitchn-203516', image_url: 'https://cdn.apartmenttherapy.info/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:eco,c_fit,w_1460/https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.googleapis.com%2Fgen-atmedia%2F3%2F2014%2F05%2F48b592862e7c9969e57ddce40caa4fac8b10955b.jpeg', mood_id: 8)
Food.create(name: 'Saag Paneer Pizza', description: 'Saag paneer is a spiced, creamy spinach stew finished with soft pieces of mild paneer cheese. The main topping for this pizza version is basically a sauté of frozen spinach with onion, garlic, ginger, and garam masala. It gets its rich flavor and texture from the addition of cream at the end, which works to hold everything together.', recipe_url: 'https://www.thekitchn.com/recipe-saag-paneer-pizza-230117', image_url: 'https://cdn.apartmenttherapy.info/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:eco,c_fit,w_1460/https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.googleapis.com%2Fgen-atmedia%2F3%2F2016%2F06%2F02fb9e5e7cf763506cb18d4185c22f5f37651fe3.jpeg', mood_id: 9)
Food.create(name: 'Hot as a Torch! Baked Jalapeño Poppers', description: 'We go right for Cabot cheese, which is owned by a co-operative of 1,100 farm families throughout New England and New York. The Cabot farmers raise happy cows because happy cows produce rich, buttery milk that becomes cheese that wins awards year after year.', recipe_url: 'https://www.thekitchn.com/3-cheesy-recipes-for-your-game-day-bash-240961', image_url: 'https://cdn.apartmenttherapy.info/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:eco,c_fit,w_1460/https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.googleapis.com%2Fgen-atmedia%2F3%2F2017%2F01%2Fd6f82b1a2feafafc0d7945e62777f4c3eeae4766.jpeg', mood_id: 10)
Food.create(name: 'Lyonnaise Salad', description: 'We have a lot to thank France for when it comes to mealtime, but perhaps one of my favorites is Lyonnaise Salad, or Salade Lyonniase: it’s a perfect combination of frisée, a curly bitter salad green, tossed in a warm vinaigrette and topped with a poached egg and crispy thick-slab bacon pieces. It’s one of those timeless dishes that hits the spot every time and can transport you to the banks of the Seine even if you’re stuck in your sweltering American apartment.', recipe_url: 'https://www.thekitchn.com/recipe-lyonnaise-salad-recipes-from-the-kitchn-4418', image_url: 'https://cdn.apartmenttherapy.info/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:eco,c_fit,w_1460/https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.googleapis.com%2Fgen-atmedia%2F3%2F2014%2F07%2F0659fbc5cb007e0009ab5c7d6e430aa6c1527eb6.jpeg', mood_id: 11)
Food.create(name: 'Honey-Sesame Tofu and Green Beans', description: 'Perhaps the most time-intensive element of this recipe is waiting for the tofu to dry out. That’s when you do the rest of the prep — making the sauce and cutting the veggies — so by the time you pop everything into the oven to cook, the 10 minutes or so it takes goes by in a flash. Would you expect anything less from a recipe from Damn Delicious?', recipe_url: 'https://www.thekitchn.com/recipe-sheet-pan-sesame-tofu-and-green-beans-235980', image_url: 'https://cdn.apartmenttherapy.info/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:eco,c_fit,w_1460/https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.googleapis.com%2Fgen-atmedia%2F3%2F2016%2F09%2Fc0f5fc5b67c1369bcb12c6645532a084a3622289.jpeg', mood_id: 12)
Food.create(name: 'Polenta with Spring Vegetable Ragout', description: 'We’re sharing the details of an Italian Polenta Supper featuring lots of toppings, like hearty braised beef, on a bed of creamy cornmeal polenta. For a lighter, vegan-friendly accompaniment to polenta, let me suggest this spring vegetable ragout. Like the braised beef, it’s rustic and uncomplicated yet completely dinner-party worthy. Make it now if you’re already basking in the glow of peas and asparagus, or save this recipe so you can celebrate the moment spring arrives.', recipe_url: 'https://www.thekitchn.com/recipe-polenta-with-spring-vegetable-ragout-recipes-from-the-kitchn-186581', image_url: 'https://cdn.apartmenttherapy.info/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:eco,c_fit,w_1460/https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.googleapis.com%2Fgen-atmedia%2F3%2F2013%2F03%2Fd9ed19fd317cd28c37e915fb0c948bcd4296b402.jpeg', mood_id: 13)
Food.create(name: 'Garlic Butter Steak and Potatoes', description: 'When you’re hankering for a classic steak and potatoes dinner, this one-skillet dish fits the bill perfectly. What makes it extra special is the garlicky lemon-parsley butter that’s basted over the steak as it’s seared. You end up with all the flavors of a steakhouse, except from the comfort of your own home.', recipe_url: 'https://www.thekitchn.com/garlic-steak-and-potatoes-258348', image_url: 'https://cdn.apartmenttherapy.info/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:eco,c_fit,w_1460/https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.googleapis.com%2Fgen-atmedia%2F3%2F2018%2F07%2F85cec2ec415704ce1e9bbe3cd9cff9a0aef40fe2.jpeg', mood_id: 14)
Food.create(name: 'Cold Peanut Sesame Noodles with Chicken', description: 'Cold may be a strong word to use for this dish — it’s really more room temperature if you serve it right away, but it tastes great leftover, straight out of the fridge, so change the name as you wish. Chilly Peanut Sesame Noodles just didn’t sound quite right to me.', recipe_url: 'https://www.thekitchn.com/recipe-cold-peanut-sesame-noodles-with-chicken-53032', image_url: 'https://cdn.apartmenttherapy.info/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:eco,c_fit,w_1460/https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.googleapis.com%2Fgen-atmedia%2F3%2F2015%2F08%2F3507c1c91499eca784208cd7d684db89c99b76a3.jpeg', mood_id: 15)
Food.create(name: 'French Onion Soup Grilled Cheese', description: 'My ultimate “bowl” of onion soup is one part soup, one part toasted bread, and one part melty cheese. Not exactly the ratio the French stand behind, but it works for me. Why not make a “quickie” French onion soup grilled cheese?', recipe_url: 'https://www.thekitchn.com/recipe-french-onion-soup-grilled-cheese-recipes-from-the-kitchn-182119', image_url: 'https://cdn.apartmenttherapy.info/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:eco,c_fit,w_1460/https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.googleapis.com%2Fgen-atmedia%2F3%2F2013%2F01%2Fe336298cf1055bead49101085cd3dc6b3933d979.jpeg', mood_id: 16)

